This rating only includes titles that have at least 4 votes. The bayesian estimate is a statistical technique used to reduce the noise due to low sample counts. In effect, the less a title has votes, the more it is pulled towards the mean (7.7101). In other words, these are the titles that many people agree are great.
 (formula)
 bayesian rating = (v ÷ (v+m)) × R + (m ÷ (v+m)) × C
 where:
  R = average for the manga
  v = number of votes for the manga
  m = minimum votes required to be listed (currently 4)
  C = the mean vote across the whole report (currently 7.7101)
